"Usakinishaji wa moduli za Perl zinazotakiwa ni rahisi zaidi kama ukitumia "
"vifurushi vilivyopo: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/installation/applications.xml:5
msgid "Additional applications"
msgstr "Programu-tumizi za ziada"

#. type: Content of: <section><abstract><para>
#: en/content/installation/applications.xml:9
msgid ""
"You can install additional application packages to extend the functionality "
"of the OTRS framework. This can be done via the package manager from the "
"Admin page, which downloads the applications from an online repository and "
"manages package dependencies. It is also possible to install packages from "
"local files."
msgstr ""
"Unaweza kusakinisha vifurushi vya ziada vya programu tumizi kupanua sifa za "
"kiunzi cha OTRS. Hii inaweza kufanyika kupitia meneja vifurushi kutoka "
"kwenye kurasa ya Msimamizi, ambayo inapakua  programu tumizi kutoka kwenye "
"hifadhi ya mtandaoni na kusimamia utegemezi wa vifurushi. Pia inawezekana "
"kusakinisha vifurushi kutoka kwenye mafaili ya ndani."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/applications.xml:15
msgid "FAQ"
msgstr "Maswali yanasoulizwa mara kwa mara"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/applications.xml:18
msgid ""
"The FAQ is the Knowledge Base component. It supports editing and viewing of "
"FAQ articles. Articles can be viewed and restricted to agents, customer "
"users, or anonymous users. These can also be structured into groups, and be "
"read in different languages."
msgstr ""
"Maswali Yanayoulizwa Mara kwa Mara ni kijenzi cha msingi wa maarifa. "
"Inaruhusu kuhariri na kuona makala za Maswali Yanayoulizwa Mara kwa Mara. "
"Makala yanaweza kuonwa na kuzuiwa kwa wakala, wateja watumiaji, au watumiaji "
"wasiojulikana. Hizi pia zinaweza kupangwa katika makundi, na kusomwa katika "
"lugha tofauti."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:7
msgid "Installation from source (Linux, Unix)"
msgstr "Usaninishaji kutoka kwenye chanzo (Linux, Unix)"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:10
msgid "Step 1: Install .tar.gz"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:12
msgid ""
"If you want to install OTRS from source, first download the source archive "
"as .tar.gz, .tar.bz2, or .zip file from <ulink url=\"http://www.otrs.com/try/"
"\">http://www.otrs.com/try/</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:17
msgid ""
"Unpack the archive (for example, using <command>tar</command>) into the "
"directory <filename>/opt</filename>, and rename the directory from otrs-x.x."
"x to otrs (see Script below)."
msgstr ""
"Pakua nyaraka (kwa mfano, kwa kutumia <command>tar</command>) kwenda kwenye "
"mpangilio orodha <filename>/opt</filename>, na upa mpangilio orodha jina "
"jipya kutoka otrs-x.x.x kuwa otrs (ona Hati chini)."

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> tar xzf /tmp/otrs-x.x.x.tar.gz\n"
"shell> mv otrs-x.x.x /opt/otrs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:29
msgid "Step 2: Install Additional Perl Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.CheckModules.pl\n"
"o CGI..............................ok (v3.60)\n"
"o Crypt::PasswdMD5.................ok (v1.3)\n"
"o Crypt::SSLeay....................Not installed! (Optional - Required for Generic Interface SOAP SSL connections.)\n"
"o CSS::Minifier....................ok (v0.01)\n"
"o Date::Format.....................ok (v2.22)\n"
"o Date::Pcalc......................ok (v1.2)\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:31
msgid ""
"Use the following script to get an overview of all installed and required "
"cpan modules.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> To install missing "
"Perl modules, you can:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:49
msgid ""
"a) Install the packages via the package manager of your Linux distribution"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> yum install \"perl(Digest::MD5)\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:54
msgid ""
"For Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora or compatible systems: <placeholder type=\"screen"
"\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> zypper search Digest::MD5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> zypper install perl-Digest-MD5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:63
msgid ""
"For SUSE Linux Enterprise Server, openSUSE or compatible systems: first "
"determine the name of the package the module is shipped in.  Usually the "
"package for My::Module would be called \"perl-My-Module\".  <placeholder "
"type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Then install: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id="
"\"1\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> apt-cache search Digest::MD5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> apt-get install libdigest-md5-perl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:80
msgid ""
"For Debian, Ubuntu or compatible systems first determine the name of the "
"package the module is shipped in.  Usually the package for My::Module would "
"be called \"libmy-module-perl\".  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> "
"Then install: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"1\"/> Please note that it "
"might be that you can't find all modules or their required versions in your "
"distribution repository, in that case you might choose to install those "
"modules via CPAN (see below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:102
msgid "b) Install the required modules via the CPAN shell"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> perl -MCPAN -e shell;\n"
"...\n"
"install Digest::MD5\n"
"install Crypt::PasswdMD5\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:104
msgid ""
"Note that when you're on Linux you should run CPAN as your superuser account "
"because the modules should be accessible both by the OTRS account and the "
"account under which the web server is running.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" "
"id=\"0\"/> Any optional modules listed by the script should be installed "
"depending on the special requirements of the target system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:124
msgid "Step 3: Create OTRS User"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> useradd -d /opt/otrs/ -c 'OTRS user' otrs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> usermod -G www otrs\n"
"(SUSE=www, Red Hat/CentOS/Fedora=apache, Debian/Ubuntu=www-data)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:126
msgid ""
"Create user: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Add user to webserver "
"group (if the webserver is not running as the OTRS user): <placeholder type="
"\"screen\" id=\"1\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:141
msgid "Step 4: Activate Default Config Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> cp Kernel/Config.pm.dist Kernel/Config.pm\n"
"shell> cp Kernel/Config/GenericAgent.pm.dist Kernel/Config/GenericAgent.pm\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:143
msgid ""
"There are two OTRS config files bundled in $OTRS_HOME/Kernel/*.dist and "
"$OTRS_HOME/Kernel/Config/*.dist. You must activate them by copying them "
"without the \".dist\" filename extension.  <placeholder type=\"screen\" id="
"\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:157
msgid "Step 5: Check if all needed modules are installed"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> perl -cw /opt/otrs/bin/cgi-bin/index.pl\n"
"/opt/otrs/bin/cgi-bin/index.pl syntax OK\n"
"\n"
"shell> perl -cw /opt/otrs/bin/cgi-bin/customer.pl\n"
"/opt/otrs/bin/cgi-bin/customer.pl syntax OK\n"
"\n"
"shell> perl -cw /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl\n"
"/opt/otrs/bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl syntax OK\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:159
msgid ""
"<placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> \"syntax OK\" tells you all "
"mandatory perl modules are installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:175
msgid "Step 6: Configuring the Apache web server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:177
msgid ""
"First of all, you should install the Apache2 web server and mod_perl; you'd "
"typically do this from your systems package manager.  Below you'll find the "
"commands needed to set up Apache on the most popular Linux distributions."
msgstr ""
"Kwanza kabisa, unatakiwa kusanidi seva ya wavuti ya Apache2 na mod_perl; "
"utafanya hivi kutoka kwenye meneja kifurushi. Hapa chini utakuta amri "
"zinazohitajika kuseti Apache kwenye usambazaji wa Linux maarufu."

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# rhel / centos:\n"
"shell> yum install httpd mod_perl\n"
"\n"
"# suse:\n"
"shell> zypper install apache2-mod_perl\n"
"\n"
"# debian/ubuntu:\n"
"shell> apt-get install apache2 libapache2-mod-perl2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:195
msgid ""
"To access the web interface of OTRS via a short URL, Alias and ScriptAlias "
"entries are needed. Most <application>Apache</application> installations "
"have a <filename>conf.d</filename> directory included. On Linux systems you "
"can usually find this directory under <filename>/etc/apache</filename> or "
"<filename>/etc/apache2</filename>. Log in as root, change to the "
"<filename>conf.d</filename> directory and copy the appropriate template in "
"<filename>/opt/otrs/scripts/apache2-httpd.include.conf</filename> to a file "
"called <filename>otrs.conf</filename> in the Apache configuration directory."
msgstr ""
"Kufikia kiolesura cha wavuti cha OTRS kupitia URL fupi, maingizo ya Lakabu "
"na HatiLakabu yanahitajika. Usakinishaji mwingi wa <application>Apache</"
"application>  una mpangilio orodha <filename>conf.d</filename> umejumuishwa. "
"Kwenye mifumo ya Linux unaweza kukuta huu mpangilio orodha chini ya "
"<filename>/etc/apache</filename> or <filename>/etc/apache2</filename>. Ingia "
"kama mzizi, badilisha kwenda mpangilio orodha <filename>conf.d</filename> na "
"nakili kiolezo husika katika <filename>/opt/otrs/scripts/apache2-httpd."
"include.conf</filename> kwenda kwenye faili liitwalo <filename>otrs.conf</"
"filename> katika mpangilio orodha wa usanidi wa Apache."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:200
msgid ""
"Restart your web server to load the new configuration settings. On most "
"systems you can start/restart your web server with the command <command>/etc/"
"init.d/apache2 restart</command>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:204
msgid "Now your web server should be configured for OTRS."
msgstr "Sasa seva yako ya wavuti inabidi iwe na usanidi wa OTRS."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:209
msgid "Step 7: File Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><cmdsynopsis>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:214
msgid ""
"<command>otrs.SetPermissions.pl</command> <arg choice='opt'> --otrs-user= "
"<replaceable>OTRS user, defaults to 'otrs'</replaceable> </arg> <arg "
"choice='req'> --web-group= <replaceable>group of the web server user</"
"replaceable> </arg>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:211
msgid ""
"File permissions need to be adjusted to allow OTRS to read and write files: "
"<placeholder type=\"cmdsynopsis\" id=\"0\"/> For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> bin/otrs.SetPermissions.pl --web-user=otrs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:256
msgid "Step 8: Database Setup and Basic System Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:258
msgid ""
"Please use the web installer at <ulink url=\"http://yourhost/otrs/installer."
"pl\">http://yourhost/otrs/installer.pl</ulink> (replace \"yourhost\" with "
"your OTRS hostname) to setup your database and basic system settings such as "
"email accounts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:263
msgid "Step 9: First login"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:265
msgid ""
"Now you are ready to login to your system at <ulink url=\"http://yourhost/"
"otrs/index.pl\">http://yourhost/otrs/index.pl</ulink> with the credentials "
"you configured in the web installer (User: root@localhost)."
